[00:32:35] Participant 32: "We talked afterwards, just reminiscing and then she said something very odd, like if only I had been faster, maybe I could have made a difference."

[00:32:40] Participant 32: "If only I'd been faster, maybe I could have made a difference" is what she says. 
[00:32:57] Participant 33: Okay. If only I had been faster… [00:33:00] Oh, she saw it, she's a witness. 
[00:33:13] Participant 32: Well, she might have been…maybe I'd been faster trying to talk to Nick. 
[00:33:17] Participant 33: Yes.

Maybe…[00:33:36] Participant 32: "Before I could ask her what she meant, Nolan came over and she started telling him about a job opening for a fry cook at Limestone Diner. He was grateful for the lead, we'd all been struggling to find work since Old Scratch closed. It's hard to believe we'll ever find another job as great." 
 "Went over to her house hoping I could talk to her about the night Nick died, said she'd been having a rough time that night, was [00:34:00] preoccupied with some work problems. Then I decided to go for a drive to try and clear my thoughts, but it only got worse from there. When I asked about the stuff she left at the bar, she got very anxious and said, we shouldn't talk here, and hustled me out the house in a hurry."
